## 6. **Accessibility Considerations**

Ensure your table is accessible to all users, including those using screen readers.

### **a. Use Semantic HTML**

- `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<th>`, `<td>`: Proper semantic elements.
- `scope` attribute for `<th>`: Defines the scope of headers.

```html
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col">Product</th>
      <th scope="col">Price</th>
      <th scope="col">Stock</th>
      <th scope="col">Category</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Apple iPhone 14</td>
      <td>$999</td>
      <td>150</td>
      <td>Electronics</td>
    </tr>
    <!-- Additional rows -->
  </tbody>
</table>
```

### **b. Associate Data Cells with Headers**

Use `headers` attribute for complex tables.

```html
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th id="prod">Product</th>
      <th id="price">Price</th>
      <th id="stock">Stock</th>
      <th id="cat">Category</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td headers="prod">Apple iPhone 14</td>
      <td headers="price">$999</td>
      <td headers="stock">150</td>
      <td headers="cat">Electronics</td>
    </tr>
    <!-- Additional rows -->
  </tbody>
</table>
```

### **c. Keyboard Navigation**

Ensure users can navigate the table using the keyboard.

- **Tabindex**: Allow cells to be focusable.
- **ARIA Roles**: Define roles for assistive technologies.

```html
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th tabindex="0" role="columnheader">Product</th>
      <th tabindex="0" role="columnheader">Price</th>
      <th tabindex="0" role="columnheader">Stock</th>
      <th tabindex="0" role="columnheader">Category</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td tabindex="0" role="cell">Apple iPhone 14</td>
      <td tabindex="0" role="cell">$999</td>
      <td tabindex="0" role="cell">150</td>
      <td tabindex="0" role="cell">Electronics</td>
    </tr>
    <!-- Additional rows -->
  </tbody>
</table>
```

